olf Harris]], Australian-born entertainer\n* [[March 31]] \n** [[Juli\u00e1n Herranz Casado]], Spanish cardinal \n** [[Alfr\u00e9d Jindra]], Czechoslovak sprint canoer (d. [[2006]])\n\n=== April ===\n[[File:Helmut Kohl 1989.jpg|thumb|100px|[[Helmut Kohl]]]]\n[[File:Bradford Dillman 1966.JPG|100px|thumb|[[Bradford Dillman]]]]\n[[File:Dick Sargent headshot.jpg|100px|thumb|[[Dick Sargent]]]]\n[[File:James A. Baker III, U.S. Secretary of State (2380044355).jpg|100px|thumb|[[James Baker]]]]\n[[File:Carolyn Jones 1956.jpg|100px|thumb|[[Carolyn Jones]]]]\n* [[April 1]] \n** [[Betsy Jones-Moreland]], American actress (d. [[2006]])\n** [[Grace Lee Whitney]], American actress (''[[Star Trek]]'') (d. [[2015]])\n* [[April 2]] \n** [[Don Hall (ice hockey)|Don Hall]], Canadian ice hockey player (d. [[2017]]) \n** [[Roddy Maude-Roxby]], English actor and artist \n* [[April 3]]\n** [[Lawton Chiles]], American politician, [[U.S. Senator]] ([[Florida]]), 41st [[Governor of Florida]] (d. [[1998]])\n** [[Helmut Kohl]], [[Chancellor of Germany (Federal Republic)|Chancellor of Germany]] (d. [[2017]])\n* [[April 4]] &ndash; [[Netty Herawaty]], Indonesian actress (d. [[1989]])\n* [[April 5]]\n** [[Mary Costa]], American opera singer and actress \n** [[Dov Lando]], Israeli rabbi\n** [[Pierre Lhomme]], French cinematographer (d. [[2019]])\n* [[April 6]] \u2013 [[Pampero Firpo]], Argentinian/American professional wrestler (d. [[2020]])\n* [[April 7]] \n** [[Vilma Esp\u00edn]], Cuban revolutionary, feminist, and chemical engineer (d. [[2007]])\n** [[Jane Priestman]], English designer \n** [[Andrew Sachs]], German-born British actor (d. [[2016]])\n* [[April 8]] &ndash; [[Carlos Hugo, Duke of Parma]] (d. [[2010]])\n* [[April 9]] &ndash; [[F. Albert Cotton]], American chemist (d. [[2007]])\n* [[April 10]] \n** [[Vladimir Yerokhin]], Russian footballer (d. [[1996]])\n** [[Claude Bolling]], French jazz pianist, composer\n** [[Spede Pasanen]], Finnish television personality (d. [[2001]])\n** [[Frank