, Chinese pharmaceutical chemist, [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine|Nobel Prize]] laureate\n* [[December 31]]\n** [[Odetta]], American singer (d. [[2008]])\n** [[Jaime Escalante]], American high school math teacher (d. [[2010]])\n\n===Unknown===\n* [[Umar Ghalib]], 7th Prime Minister of Somalia\n\n==Deaths==\n\n===January \u2013 June===\n[[File:AhmadShahQajar2.jpg|thumb|100px|[[Ahmad Shah Qajar]]]]\n[[File:William Howard Taft cph.3b35813.jpg|thumb|100px|[[William Howard Taft]]]]\n[[File:Bundesarchiv Bild 102-09414, Primo de Rivera.jpg|thumb|100px|[[Miguel Primo de Rivera]]]]\n[[File:Gws balfour 02.jpg|thumb|100px|[[Arthur Balfour]]]]\n[[File:KevorkVofArmenia.jpg|thumb|100px|Patriarch [[George V of Armenia]]]]\n* [[January 3]] &ndash; [[Guglielmo Pl\u00fcschow]], German photographer (b. [[1852]])\n* [[January 9]] &ndash; [[Edward Bok]], American author (b. [[1863]])\n* [[January 13]] &ndash; [[John Nathan Cobb]], American author, naturalist, conservationist, fisheries researcher, and educator (b. [[1868]])\n* [[January 19]] &ndash; [[Frank P. Ramsey]], British philosopher, mathematician and economist (b. [[1903]])\n* [[January 22]] &ndash; [[Reginald Brett, 2nd Viscount Esher]], British politician and courtier (b. [[1852]])\n* [[January 27]] &ndash; [[Dewa Shiget\u014d]], Japanese admiral (b. [[1856]])\n* [[February 3]] \n** [[Michele Bianchi]], Italian fascist leader (b. [[1883]])\n** [[Poseidon (horse)|Poseidon]], Australian racehorse (b. [[1903]])\n* [[February 14]] &ndash; [[Thomas Mackenzie|Sir Thomas MacKenzie]], New Zealand politician, explorer, 18th [[Prime Minister of New Zealand]] and High Commissioner (b. [[1854]])\n* [[February 15]] &ndash; [[Giulio Douhet]], Italian general, [[air power]] theorist (b. [[1869]])\n* [[February 21]] &ndash; [[Ahmad Shah Qajar]], [[Pahlavi dynasty|Shah of Persia]] (b. [[1898]])\n* [[February 23]]\n** [[Mabel Normand]], American actress (b. [[1892]])\n** [[Horst Wessel]], Nazi ideologue, composer (b. [[1907]])\n* [[February 26]] &ndash; [[Rafael Merry del Val]], British-born Spanish [[Roman Catholic]] cardinal and servant of God (b. [[1865]])\n* [[February 28]] &ndash; [[Perceval Maitland Laurence|Sir Perceval Maitland Laurence]], British classical scholar, South African judge and a benefactor of the University of Cambridge (b. [[1854]])\n* [[March 2]] &ndash; [[D. H. Lawrence]], British writer (''Lady Chatterley's Lover'') (b. [[1885]])\n* [[March 6]] &ndash; [[Alfred von Tirpitz]], German politician, admiral (b. [[1848]])\n* [[March 8]] &ndash; [[William Howard Taft]], 27th [[President of the United States]], 10th [[Chief Justice of the United States]] (b. [[1857]])\n* [[March 12]] &ndash; [[William George Barker]], Canadian pilot (b. [[1894]])\n* [[March 16]] &ndash; [[Miguel Primo de Rivera]], Spanish military officer, [[Prime Minister of Spain]] (b. [[1870]])\n* [[March 19]] \n** [[Arthur Balfour]], British politician and statesman, 48th [[Prime Minister of the United Kingdom]] (b. [[1848]])\n** [[Joseph Dupont (bishop)|Joseph Dupont]], French missionary, bishop (b. [[1850]])\n* [[March 24]] \n** [[Henry Faulds]], Scottish doctor, missionary and fingerprinting pioneer (b. [[1843]])\n** [[Eugeen Van Mieghem]], Belgian painter (b. [[1875]])\n* [[March 31]] &ndash; [[James Marshall Head]], American politician and businessman (b. [[1855]])\n* [[April 1]] &ndash; [[Cosima Wagner]], wife and inspiration of [[Richard Wagner]] (b. [[1837]])\n* [[April 2]] &ndash; Empress [[Zewditu]] of Ethiopia (b. [[1876]])\n* [[April 4]] &ndash; [[Victoria of Baden]], [[Queen consort of Sweden]] (b. [[1862]])\n* [[April 6]] &ndash; [[Dimitrije, Serbian Patriarch]] (b. [[1846]])\n* [[April 7]] &ndash; [[Octaviano Ambrosio Larrazolo]], American politician (b. [[1859]])\n* [[April 9]] &ndash; [[Heinrich Ritter von Wittek]], Austrian politician, statesman (b. [[1844]])\n* [[April 10]] &ndash; [[Alfred Williams (poet)|Alfred Williams]], British poet (b. [[1877]])\n* [[April 14]]\n** [[Vladimir Mayakovsky]], Russian poet (b. [[1893]])\n** [[John B. Sheridan]], Irish-American sports journalist (b. [[1870]])\n* [[April 21]] &ndash; [[Robert Bridges]], British poet (b. [[1844]])\n* [[April 22]] &ndash; [[Jeppe Aakj\u00e6r]], Danish poet, novelist (b. [[1866]])\n* [[May 8]] &ndash; Patriarch [[George V of Armenia]] (b. [[1847]])\n* [[May 13]] &ndash; [[Fridtjof Nansen]], Norwegian explorer, recipient of the [[Nobel Peace Prize]] (b. [[1861]])\n* [[May 17]] &ndash; [[Herbert Croly]], American political author (b. [[1869]])\n* [[May 25]]\n** [[Randall Davidson]], [[Archbishop of Canterbury]] (b. [[1848]])\n** [[Archduke Rainer of Austria (1895-1930)|Archduke Rainer of Austria]] (b. [[1895]]\n* [[June 5]]\n** [[Eric Lemming]], Swedish athlete (b. 1880)\n** [[Pascin]], Bulgarian painter (b. [[1885]])\n* [[June 10]] &ndash; [[Adolf von Harnack]], German Lutheran theologian, church historian (b. [[1851]])\n* [[June 13]] &ndash; [[Henry Segrave|Sir Henry Segrave]], British racer, speed record holder (b. [[1896]])\n\n===July\u2013 December===\n[[File:Conan doyle.jpg|thumb|100px|[[Sir Arthur Conan Doyle]]]]\n[[File:Sir Joseph Ward, 1928.jpg|thumb|100px|[[Joseph Ward]]]]\n[[File:Jlsanfuentes.PNG|thumb|100px|[[Juan Luis Sanfuentes]]]]\n[[File:Alfred Wegener ca.1924-30.jpg|thumb|100px|[[Alfred Wegener]]]]\n[[File:Nikolai Alexandrov.jpg|thumb|100px|[[Nikolai Alexandrov (actor)|Nikolai Alexandrov]]]]\n[[File:Vintila Bratianu - Foto01.jpg|thumb|100px|[[Vintil\u0103 Br\u0103tianu]]]]\n[[File:FACTA Luigi.gif|thumb|100px|[[Luigi Facta]]]]\n[[File:Konstantinos VI.jpg|thumb|100px|Patriarch [[Constantine VI of Constantinople|Constantine VI]]]]\n* [[July 7]] &ndash; Sir [[Arthur Conan Doyle]], British fiction writer (''[[Sherlock Holmes]]'') (b. [[1859]])\n* [[July 8]] &ndash; Sir [[Joseph Ward]], 17th [[Prime Minister of New Zealand]] (b. [[1856]])\n* [[July 15]]\n** [[Leopold Auer]], Hungarian violinist (b. [[1845]])\n** [[Rudolph Schildkraut]], Ottoman-born Austrian actor (b. [[1862]])\n