 LaVey]], American author, musician, and occultist (d. [[1997]])\n* [[April 12]] \n** [[John Landy]], Australian athlete and politician \n** [[Nancy Lyons]], Australian Olympic swimmer \n** [[Manuel Neri]], American sculptor and painter \n** [[Micha\u0142 \u017byczkowski]], Polish Professor of Engineering (d. [[2006]])\n* [[April 14]] \n** [[Bradford Dillman]], American actor, author (d. [[2018]])\n** [[Arnold Burns]], American lawyer (d. [[2013]])\n* [[April 15]] \n** [[Zhu Xu]], Chinese actor (d. [[2018]])\n** [[Vigd\u00eds Finnbogad\u00f3ttir]], [[President of Iceland]]\n* [[April 16]]\n** [[Carol Bly]], American teacher, author of short stories, essays and nonfiction (d. [[2007]])\n** [[Herbie Mann]], American jazz flutist and important (d. [[2003]])\n* [[April 17]] &ndash; [[Chris Barber]], English trombonist and bandleader \n* [[April 18]] &ndash; [[Clive Revill]], New Zealand actor and singer \n* [[April 19]]\n** [[Dick Sargent]], American actor, gay activist (d. [[1994]])\n** [[Curtis Roosevelt]], American writer (d. [[2016]])\n* [[April 21]] &ndash; [[Silvana Mangano]], Italian actress (d. [[1989]])\n* [[April 23]] &ndash; [[Shun Akiyama]], Japanese literary critic (d. [[2013]]) \n* [[April 24]]\n** [[Richard Donner]], American film director, producer\n** [[Jos\u00e9 Sarney]], 31st [[President of Brazil]]\n* [[April 25]] &ndash; [[Paul Mazursky]], American director, writer (d. [[2014]])\n* [[April 26]] &ndash; [[Roger Moens]], Belgian athlete and sportscaster \n* [[April 28]]\n** [[James Baker]], former [[United States Secretary of State]]\n** [[Carolyn Jones]], American actress (d. [[1983]])\n* [[April 29]]\n** [[Jean Rochefort]], French actor (d. [[2017]])\n** [[Henri Coppens]], Belgian football player (d. [[2015]])\n** [[Irv Weinstein]], American broadcaster, television news anchor (d. [[2017]])\n** [[Mahmud of Terengganu]], 16th Sultan of Terengganu (d. [[1998]])\n* [[April 30]] &ndash; [[F\u00e9lix Guattari]], French psychotherapist, philosopher, semio