{"title_page": "1942 (song)", "text_new": "{{for|the PartyNextDoor song|PartyNextDoor 3}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name          = 1942\n| cover         = G-Eazy 1942.png\n| type          = single\n| artist        = [[G-Eazy]] featuring [[Yo Gotti]] and [[YBN Nahmir]]\n| album         = [[Uncle Drew|Uncle Drew (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack)]]\n| released      = {{start date|2018|4|13}}\n| format        =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| genre         = [[Hip hop]]\n| length        = {{duration|m=3|s=33}}\n| label         = [[RCA Records|RCA]]\n| writer        =\n* [[G-Eazy|Gerald Gillum]]\n* [[Yo Gotti|Mario Mims]]\n* [[YBN Nahmir|Nick Simmons]]\n* [[Hitmaka|Christian Ward]]\n* [[Samuel Jimenez|Samuel David Jimenez]]\n* Edgar Ferrera\n| producer      =\n* [[Hitmaka]]\n* [[Smash David]]\n* SkipOnDaBeat\n| chronology    = [[G-Eazy]]\n| prev_title    = [[Sober (G-Eazy song)|Sober]]\n| prev_year     = 2017\n| next_title    = Reverse\n| next_year     = 2018\n| misc          = {{Extra chronology\n | artist       = [[Yo Gotti]]\n | type         = single\n | prev_title   = Juice\n | prev_year    = 2017\n | title        = 1942\n | year         = 2018\n | next_title   = Wraith\n | next_year    = 2018\n }}\n{{Extra chronology\n | artist       = [[YBN Nahmir]]\n | type         = single\n | prev_title   = Bounce Out with That\n | prev_year    = 2018\n | title        = 1942\n | year         = 2018\n | next_title   = Baby 8\n | next_year    = 2019\n }}\n{{External music video|{{YouTube|rDl3gAJpm_4|\"1942\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''1942'''\" is a song by American rapper [[G-Eazy]], featuring guest vocals from rappers [[Yo Gotti]] and [[YBN Nahmir]]. The artists co-wrote the song with its producers [[Hitmaka]], [[Samuel Jimenez|Smash David]] and SkipOnDaBeat.<ref>{{cite news|title=G-Eazy, Yo Gotti & YBN Nahmir Connect For \"1942\" Heater|url=https://hiphopdx.com/singles/id.36681/title.g-eazy-yo-gotti-ybn-nahmir-connect-for-1942-heater#|accessdate=May 13, 2018|work=HipHopDX|date=April 16, 2018}}</ref> It was released by [[RCA Records]] on April 13, 2018, as the second single for the soundtrack to the film ''[[Uncle Drew (film)|Uncle Drew]]'' (2018).<ref>{{cite news|last=Mitchell|first=Gail|title=RCA's Mark Pitts Celebrates 20th Anniversary of ByStorm Entertainment|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8343827/rca-mark-pitts-20th-anniversary-bystorm-entertainment|accessdate=May 13, 2018|work=Billboard|date=April 17, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\n\"1942\" features a \"hypnotic and bouncy production\" from Hitmaka and \"a catchy hook\" provided by Gotti.<ref>{{cite news|last=Price|first=Joe|title=Yo Gotti and YBN Nahmir Join G-Eazy on \"1942\"|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2018/04/yo-gotti-and-ybn-nahmir-collab-with-g-eazy-for-1942|accessdate=May 13, 2018|work=Complex|date=April 14, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=New Music: G-Eazy feat. Yo Gotti & YBN Nahmir \u2013 '1942'|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2018/04/13/new-music-g-eazy-yo-gotti-ybn-nahmir-1942/|accessdate=May 13, 2018|work=Rap-Up|date=April 13, 2018}}</ref> Lyrically, G-Eazy raps about ignoring the rules and doing whatever he wants.<ref>{{cite news|last=Goddard|first=Kevin|title=G-Eazy Links Up With Yo Gotti & YBN Nahmir For New \"Uncle Drew\" Leak \"1942\"|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/g-eazy-links-up-with-yo-gotti-and-ybn-nahmir-for-new-uncle-drew-leak-1942-new-song.1978140.html|accessdate=May 13, 2018|work=HotNewHipHop|date=April 13, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Berry|first=Peter|title=G-Eazy, Yo Gotti and YBN Nahmir Follow Their Own Rules on New Song \"1942\"|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/rap-music/new-music/2018/04/g-eazy-yo-gotti-ybn-nahmir-1942/|accessdate=May 13, 2018|work=XXL|date=April 13, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref name=\"Tidal\">{{cite web|title=1942 / G-Eazy TIDAL|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/87259376|website=Tidal|accessdate=May 13, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Hitmaka]] \u2013 production\n* [[Samuel Jimenez|Smash David]] \u2013 production\n* SkipOnDaBeat \u2013 production\n* [[Jaycen Joshua]] \u2013 mix engineering\n* David Nakaji \u2013 engineering assistance\n* Ben Milchev \u2013 engineering assistance\n* Dakari \u2013 record engineering\n* Brian White \u2013 record engineering\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2018)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br /> position\n|-\n{{single chart|Canada|90|artist=G-Eazy|rowheader=true|accessdate=June 26, 2018}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardhot100|70|artist=G-Eazy|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 14, 2018}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardrandbhiphop|29|artist=G-Eazy|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 7, 2018}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardrhythmic|12|artist=G-Eazy|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 21, 2018}}\n|}\n\n==Certifications==\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|type=single|region=Canada|artist=G-Eazy|title=1942|award=Platinum|relyear=2018|certyear=2019}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|type=single|region=United States|artist=G-Eazy|title=1942|award=Platinum|relyear=2018|certyear=2019}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|streaming=true}}\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Region\n! scope=\"col\"| Date\n! scope=\"col\"| Format\n! scope=\"col\"| Label\n! scope=\"col\"| {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Various\n| April 13, 2018\n| {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| [[RCA Records|RCA]]\n| <ref name=\"Tidal\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\"| United States\n| rowspan=\"2\"| May 29, 2018\n| [[Rhythmic contemporary]] radio\n| rowspan=\"2\"| {{hlist|BPG|RVG|RCA}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allaccess.com/top40-rhythmic/future-releases|title=Top 40/R Future Releases|publisher=All Access Media Group|accessdate=May 13, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180513135415/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-rhythmic/future-releases|archivedate=May 13, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Urban contemporary]] radio\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allaccess.com/urban/future-releases|title=Urban/UAC Future Releases|publisher=All Access Music Group|accessdate=May 13, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180513151937/https://www.allaccess.com/urban/future-releases|archivedate=May 13, 2018}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{G-Eazy}}\n{{Yo Gotti}}\n\n[[Category:2018 songs]]\n[[Category:2018 singles]]\n[[Category:G-Eazy songs]]\n[[Category:RCA Records singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Yo Gotti]]\n[[Category:Yo Gotti songs]]\n[[Category:YBN Nahmir songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Smash David]]\n[[Category:Songs written by G-Eazy]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Yung Berg]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the PartyNextDoor song|PartyNextDoor 3}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name          = 1942\n| cover         = G-Eazy 1942.png\n| type          = single\n| artist        = [[G-Eazy]] featuring [[Yo Gotti]] and [[YBN Nahmir]]\n| album         = [[Uncle Drew|Uncle Drew (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack)]]\n| released      = {{start date|2018|4|13}}\n| format        =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| genre         = [[Hip hop]]\n| length        = {{duration|m=3|s=33}}\n| label         = [[RCA Records|RCA]]\n| writer        =\n* [[G-Eazy|Gerald Gillum]]\n* [[Yo Gotti|Mario Mims]]\n* [[YBN Nahmir|Nick Simmons]]\n* [[Hitmaka|Christian Ward]]\n* [[Samuel Jimenez|Samuel David Jimenez]]\n* Edgar Ferrera\n| producer      =\n* [[Hitmaka]]\n* [[Samuel Jimenez|Smash David]]\n* SkipOnDaBeat\n| chronology    = [[G-Eazy]]\n| prev_title    = [[Sober (G-Eazy song)|Sober]]\n| prev_year     = 2017\n| next_title    = Reverse\n| next_year     = 2018\n| misc          = {{Extra chronology\n | artist       = [[Yo Gotti]]\n | type         = single\n | prev_title   = Juice\n | prev_year    = 2017\n | title        = 1942\n | year         = 2018\n |